What is kubeconfig
The kubeconfig file is a configuration file that contains the necessary
information to connect and authenticate with a Kubernetes cluster. It
includes details such as the cluster's API server endpoint, the user's
credentials, and the default namespace.
The kubeconfig file is used by the kubectl command-line tool to interact
with the Kubernetes cluster. By updating the kubeconfig file, you can grant
access to the Kubernetes cluster for managing resources and deploying
applications.
In the context of the AWS Builder Lab, the aws eks update-kubeconfig
command is used to update the kubeconfig file with the necessary
information to connect to the Amazon EKS (Elastic Kubernetes Service)
cluster. This allows you to use kubectl to manage the resources in the EKS
cluster.
aws eks update-kubeconfig \
--region $AWS_DEFAULT_REGION \
--name eks-lab-cluster
